msgid "Number of elements (fixed at compile time)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:38
msgid "`ALIGN`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:38
msgid ""
"Byte alignment (default 0 = natural alignment; use 128 for TMA destinations)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:129
msgid ""
"`SharedArray` is `!Sync` by design — it wraps `UnsafeCell`, which prevents "
"the compiler from assuming immutability across threads. This is correct: "
"shared memory is inherently mutable by all threads in the block, and the "
"programmer is responsible for synchronization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:135
msgid "The API surface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:137
msgid ""
"impl<T, const N: usize, const ALIGN: usize> SharedArray<T, N, ALIGN> {\n"
"    pub const UNINIT: Self;\n"
"    pub const fn len() -> usize;\n"
"    pub fn as_ptr(&self) -> *const T;\n"
"    pub fn as_mut_ptr(&mut self) -> *mut T;\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"// Indexing (unsafe access via static mut)\n"
"impl Index<usize> for SharedArray<T, N, ALIGN> { ... }\n"
"impl IndexMut<usize> for SharedArray<T, N, ALIGN> { ... }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:150
msgid ""
"Indexing is bounds-checked in debug builds. In release (and on the GPU), the "
"bounds check is elided. If you index out of bounds, you get undefined "
"behavior — the same rules as any `static mut` access in Rust."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:156
msgid "DynamicSharedArray — runtime-sized allocation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:158
msgid ""
"Sometimes you do not know the tile size at compile time, or you want to "
"share a single shared memory pool across multiple logical arrays. "
"`DynamicSharedArray` allocates from the dynamic shared memory region, whose "
"size is set at launch time via `LaunchConfig::shared_mem_bytes`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:163
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::{kernel, thread, DynamicSharedArray};\n"
"\n"
"#[kernel]\n"
"pub fn reduce_dynamic(input: &[f32], n: u32, mut output: DisjointSlice<f32>) "
"{\n"
"    let tid = thread::threadIdx_x() as usize;\n"
"\n"
"    // Get a pointer to the dynamic shared memory region\n"
"    let smem: *mut f32 = DynamicSharedArray::<f32>::get();\n"
"\n"
"    unsafe {\n"
"        // Load from global\n"
"        let idx = thread::index_1d();\n"
"        *smem.add(tid) = if idx.get() < n as usize {\n"
"            input[idx.get()]\n"
"        } else {\n"
"            0.0\n"
"        };\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    thread::sync_threads();\n"
"\n"
"    // Tree reduction\n"
"    let mut stride = thread::blockDim_x() as usize / 2;\n"
"    while stride > 0 {\n"
"        if tid < stride {\n"
"            unsafe {\n"
"                *smem.add(tid) += *smem.add(tid + stride);\n"
"            }\n"
"        }\n"
"        thread::sync_threads();\n"
"        stride /= 2;\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    if tid == 0 {\n"
"        let block_idx = thread::blockIdx_x() as usize;\n"
"        unsafe {\n"
"            *output.get_unchecked_mut(block_idx) = *smem;\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:206
msgid "Launch with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:208
msgid ""
"let config = LaunchConfig {\n"
"    grid_dim: ((n + 255) / 256, 1, 1),\n"
"    block_dim: (256, 1, 1),\n"
"    shared_mem_bytes: 256 * std::mem::size_of::<f32>() as u32,\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:216
msgid "Partitioning dynamic shared memory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:218
msgid "If you need multiple arrays from the same dynamic pool, use `offset()`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:220
msgid ""
"let pool_a: *mut f32 = DynamicSharedArray::<f32>::get();\n"
"let pool_b: *mut f32 = DynamicSharedArray::<f32>::offset(\n"
"    256 * std::mem::size_of::<f32>()\n"
");\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:227
msgid ""
"`offset` takes a **byte offset** from the start of the pool. Make sure the "
"total does not exceed `shared_mem_bytes` — there are no runtime guards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:230
msgid "Alignment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:232
msgid ""
"`DynamicSharedArray` defaults to 16-byte alignment. For TMA operations "
"(Hopper+), use `DynamicSharedArray<f32, 128>` to get the required 128-byte "
"alignment. The alignment is encoded in the PTX `.align` directive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:238
msgid "Synchronization: sync_threads()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:240
msgid ""
"`thread::sync_threads()` is a **block-wide barrier**. It compiles to PTX "
"`bar.sync 0` and guarantees two things:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:243
msgid ""
"**All threads in the block** have reached the barrier before any proceed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:244
msgid ""
"**All memory writes** by those threads are visible to all threads after the "
"barrier (it acts as a memory fence for shared memory)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:247
msgid ""
"Without `sync_threads()` between the load and compute phases, some threads "
"might read a shared memory location before another thread has written it. "
"The hardware does not guarantee any ordering within a warp for shared memory "
"stores — even threads in the same warp can see stale values without a "
"barrier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:253
msgid "When to sync"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:255
msgid "The rule is simple: **sync before reading what another thread wrote**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:128
msgid "Situation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:128
msgid "Need sync?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:128
msgid "Thread A writes `TILE[i]`, Thread B reads `TILE[i]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:128
msgid "Yes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:128
msgid "Thread A writes `TILE[i]`, Thread A reads `TILE[i]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:128
msgid "No (same thread)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:128
msgid "Overwriting a tile for the next loop iteration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:128
msgid ""
"Yes (before the new load overwrites data threads might still be reading)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:128
msgid "Reading from `DisjointSlice` (each thread reads its own index)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:128
msgid "No"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:264
msgid ""
"The tiled GEMM above has two sync points per iteration: one after loading "
"(before computing) and one after computing (before the next load overwrites "
"the tile). Missing either one is a data race."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/shared-memory-and-synchronization.md:269
msgid ""
"A common mistake is putting `sync_threads()` inside a conditional branch "
"that not all threads take. Every thread in the block must reach the same "
"`sync_threads()` call, or the kernel will deadlock. If you need divergent "
"control flow, restructure so the barrier is outside the branch."
msgstr ""

